# Spring Boot Unit Testing

## Slice Tests
- `@WebMvcTest(Controller.class)` for controller layer tests
- `@DataJdbcTest` for Spring Data JDBC repository tests
- `@DataJpaTest` for Spring Data JPA repository tests (auto-configures embedded DB, JPA, and Hibernate)
- `@JsonTest` for JSON serialization/deserialization tests
- Slice tests load only the relevant Spring context slice

## MockMvc
- Use `MockMvc` to test controllers without starting a full server
- Test HTTP method, path, request body, status code, response body
- Verify response structure with `jsonPath()` assertions

## Mocking
- `@MockitoBean` (Spring Boot 4.x) to replace beans in the test context
- `@MockitoSpyBean` for partial mocking
- Mockito `when().thenReturn()` for stubbing, `verify()` for interaction checks

## Test Structure
- Given-When-Then pattern
- One assertion concept per test
- Descriptive test names: `shouldReturnUserWhenIdExists`
- `@DisplayName` for readable test output

## Configuration
- Test properties in `src/test/resources/application-test.yml`
- `@ActiveProfiles("test")` to activate test profile
- Use `@TestConfiguration` for test-specific beans

## Anti-Patterns
- Loading full application context for unit tests (`@SpringBootTest`)
- Testing Spring internals instead of behavior
- Shared mutable state between tests

